ies** - Data access\n   - Extend `JpaRepository<Entity, Long>` for CRUD\n   - Some extend `JpaSpecificationExecutor<Entity>` for dynamic queries\n   - Use `@Query` for custom JPQL/SQL queries\n   - Marked with `@Repository` stereotype annotation\n\n**Dependency Injection Pattern**:\n```java\n@Service\n@RequiredArgsConstructor  // Lombok generates constructor with all final fields\npublic class EntityServiceImpl implements EntityService {\n    private final EntityRepository entityRepository;\n    \n    @Qualifier(\"IngestionIdService\")  // Disambiguate when multiple implementations exist\n    private final IdService idService;\n    \n    private final PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager;\n    private final MeterRegistry meterRegistry;\n}\n```\n\nAll DI is **constructor-based** using Lombok's `@RequiredArgsConstructor`. Controllers use `@Resource` annotation for field injection on EntityService.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Transaction Boundaries & Management**\n\n**Transaction Configuration**:\n\n1. **Service-Level Transactions**:\n   - `EntityServiceImpl` methods marked with `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)`\n   - Creates NEW transactions independent of outer transaction context\n   - Used to ensure updates are committed even if caller's transaction rolls back\n\n2. **Explicit Transaction Management**:\n   ```java\n   @Value(\"${policy.reprocess.mark-init-batch-size:1000}\")\n   private int markInitBatchSize;\n   \n   // Uses TransactionTemplate for fine-grained batch control\n   TransactionTemplate batchTx = new TransactionTemplate(transactionManager);\n   batchTx.setPropagationBehavior(TransactionDefinition.PROPAGATION_REQUIRES_NEW);\n   batchTx.execute(status -> entityRepository.markBatchForReprocess(batchIds, state));\n   ```\n\n3. **Stage Processing Transactions**:\n   - `EntityStageTransactionRunner` wraps stage execution with `@Transactional`\n   - `StageExecutor` uses `TransactionAspectSupport.currentTransactionStatus().setRollbackOnly()` for error handling\n   - Checks `TransactionSynchronizationManager.isActualTransactionActive()` before marking rollback\n\n4. **Repository-Level Modifications**:\n   - `@Modifying(clearAutomatically = true, flushAutomatically = true)` on `@Query` updates\n   - Automatically clears Hibernate session and flushes changes after execution\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Query Endpoints Summary**\n\n**EntityController Endpoints**:\n- `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}` - Fetch entity by ID (via `entityService.getById()`)\n- `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` - Get entity display status with state mapping\n- `POST /api/v1/entities/query` - Search failed entities with pagination, filtering, sorting\n\n**Other Controllers**:\n- `IngestionController.POST /api/v1/ingestion/events` - Async event ingestion (uses reactive Mono)\n- `IngestionController.GET /api/v1/ingestion/health-check` - Health endpoint\n- `FingerprintController.POST /api/v1/fingerprint/calculate` - Calculate entity fingerprint\n- `PolicyController.POST /api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` - Mark all entities for reprocessing\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Configuration Classes**\n\n**Key Configuration Beans**:\n\n- **IdGeneratorConfig** (`IdGeneratorConfig.java`): \n  - Registers `ingestionIdGenerator` bean (Snowflake ID generator)\n  - Qualifier: `@Qualifier(\"IngestionIdService\")` for IdService\n\n- **NettyOffLoadThreadPoolConfig** (`NettyOffLoadThreadPoolConfig.java`):\n  - Creates `nettyOffloadExecutor` bean (ThreadPoolExecutor)\n  - Micrometer metrics integration\n\n- **PolicyReprocessAsyncConfig** (`PolicyReprocessAsyncConfig.java`):\n  - `policyReprocessListenerExecutor` - For event listeners\n  - `policyReprocessJobExecutor` - For batch jobs\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Application Bootstrap**\n\n**File**: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/IngestionApplication.java`\n\n```java\n@EnableAsync\n@EnableScheduling\n@SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = \"com.fortinet.nac\")\npublic class IngestionApplication {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(IngestionApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- Enables async/scheduling for `@Async` and `@Scheduled` methods\n- Scans `com.fortinet.nac` package (includes common, classification, ingestion modules)\n\n---\n\n## ARCHITECTURAL INSIGHTS & RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n### **Strengths**:\n\n1. **Clean Separation of Concerns**: Three-tier architecture (Controller → Service → Repository) is well-maintained\n2. **Constructor Injection**: Prevents circular dependencies, makes dependencies explicit via Lombok\n3. **Transaction Management**: Explicit use of `REQUIRES_NEW` propagation for fault-tolerant batch operations\n4. **JPA Abstraction**: Uses Spring Data JPA's `JpaRepository` and `JpaSpecificationExecutor` for flexible querying\n5. **Reactive Web Layer**: Reactive controllers for async HTTP handling without blocking\n6. **Metrics Integration**: Micrometer integration for monitoring thread pools and operation timing\n7. **Error Handling in Stages**: Transaction rollback support via `StageExecutor` with explicit status checks\n\n### **Potential Considerations**:\n\n1. **No Explicit UnitOfWork Pattern**: Could use Hibernate Session management more explicitly for complex scenarios\n2. **Service Layer Granularity**: Some services (e.g., `FingerprintServiceImpl`) orchestrate across multiple repositories without transactional boundaries\n3. **Batch Operations**: Uses `TransactionTemplate` directly in service logic rather than delegating to repository\n4. **Interface Segregation**: Some service interfaces could be split further (e.g., EntityService is fairly large with ~15 methods)\n\n### **Recommended Patterns**:\n\n1. For new GET endpoints, follow `EntityController.getEntity()` pattern: simple delegation to service → repository\n2. For complex entity queries, use `JpaSpecificationExecutor` like in `EntityServiceImpl.queryFailedEntities()`\n3. For batch updates, use `TransactionTemplate` with `REQUIRES_NEW` to isolate failures\n4. Leverage `@Query` with `@Modifying` for atomic update operations\n5. Always inject via constructor with `@RequiredArgsConstructor` (Lombok)\n\n---\n\n## File Reference Summary\n\n| Purpose | File Path |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **Controller** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/EntityController.java` |\n| **Service Interface** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityService.java` |\n| **Service Implementation** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityServiceImpl.java` |\n| **Repository** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/repository/EntityRepository.java` |\n| **Entity Model** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/entity/Entity.java` |\n| **Transaction Runner** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/consumer/statemachine/EntityStageTransactionRunner.java` |\n| **Build Configuration** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/pom.xml` |\n| **Application Entry** | `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/IngestionApplication.java` |"}],"totalDurationMs":101510,"totalTokens":65362,"totalToolUseCount":41,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1660,"cache_read_input_tokens":58624,"output_tokens":5074,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1660},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":4,"output_tokens":5074,"cache_read_input_tokens":58624,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1660,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1660,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":31,"searchCount":0,